div.div: This bit is the offset, it's the _number_ of elements between the aligned pointer and where you want the first element to be accessed. An offset of 8 would put this line at 0x600001f1d000, i.e. aligned pointer address + 8 * sizeof(double). Accessing a memref with this offset would do a `load[0]` or `store[0]` from this line.
